0.10.2 Release : A New Toy
--------------------------

The PiTiVi team is proud to announce the third release of the 0.10.x series of the PiTiVi opensource video editor.

The goal of this series is to allow users to test new versions often, give their feedback, and remove bugs more often.


* Features of this release

 * UI improvements for usability
 * decodebin2 support
 * Rendering improvements
 * i18n support, translated in 12 languages
 * Critical bugfixes

* Bugs Fixed

 * 353859 : [discoverer] Use 'no-more-pads' information 
 * 335699 : Pitivi fails to work if project created at wrong time 
 * 335822 : Transcoding WMV creates tiny file 
 * 335826 : Cancel and restarting rendering not possible 
 * 336332 : Can't play a file in pitivi until i scrub forward 
 * 337990 : [Tracker] Need internationalization/localization 
 * 338065 : combobox next to time is useless and should go 
 * 339994 : follow the gnome toolbar and menu settings 
 * 346584 : pitivi should have intltool and gettext support 
 * 346585 : Don't use whitespace before punctuation in pitivi messages 
 * 348232 : hang when loading an ogg 
 * 350562 : Error message when transcoding 
 * 352400 : [importing] Allow importing (sub)folders 
 * 353861 : Don't close filechooser dialog box immediatly 
 * 377117 : pitivi won't start 
 * 378865 : Windows media transcoding borks with audio 
 * 381959 : Pressing Alt-F to activate file menu toggles fullscreen 
 * 381970 : Make pitivi work uninstalled from SVN repositories 
 * 382249 : configure on ubuntu edgy fails to find pygtk 
 * 383826 : Pitivi can't scroll one 0.5 sec tic at a time 
 * 392204 : pitivi crash when objectfactory doesn't have valid thumbn... 
 * 396808 : Split up code from pitivi/ to subdirectories 


* Requirements

 * gstreamer >= 0.10.8
 * gst-python >= 0.10.6
 * gnonlin >= 0.10.7
 * pygtk >= 2.8.0


